<body>

Far On Droid is a panel file manager.<br>

<div>
    <div class="floatLeftDiv">
        <img src="navigation_panels.png" alt="Panels"/>
    </div>
    <div class="floatText">
        It contains two panels: left and right (You can switch to 'single panel mode' in <strong>Settings</strong>). Panel, which currently have focus is called <strong>active panel</strong>.<br>
        If you want to make your panel active - perform any touch event on it.<br>
        You can make your panel flexible (in <strong>Settings -> Flexible Panels</strong>) and expand/constrict panels by swipe gesture.<br>
        When panel is active path on the top of panel is marked by <span style="background-color: #008080; padding:0;" >background</span>.<br>
        All file operations (like copy, move, delete) performed from active panel, i.e. if you selects a few files and call 'Copy' command files will be copied from active to inactive panel.<br>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="clear">
    <br><br>
    Click on directory if want to go into it. <span style="background-color: #008080; padding:0;">..</span>
    will bring you in the parent folder. The same will do 'Back' button (for currently active panel). Click on 'Back' button when root position (i.e. '/') is reached will close application. <br>
    Scroll your active panel to see extra elements outside the visible area.
</div>

<div class="clear">
    <br><br>
    Click on star icon <img src="add_bookmark.png" style="background-color: #008080; margin: 0; width: 16px; height: 16px"/> to add current directory to bookmarks (favorites) list (read more about bookmarks in <a href="far_help/files">FILES</a> topic).
</div>

<div class="clear">
    <br><br>
    Click on <img src="cloud.png" style="background-color: #008080; margin: 0; width: 16px; height: 16px"/> icon to open 'Select Network' dialog (where you can select one of supported network clouds/storages).
</div>

<div class="clear">
    <br><br>
    Click on <img src="home.png" style="background-color: #008080; margin: 0; width: 16px; height: 16px"/> icon (it's visible only when <strong>Settings -> Enable Home folder</strong> option is enabled) to open current home
    directory on active panel. <br/>
    <strong>Home directory</strong> - it's base directory (when enabled in settings) for your panel. It might be opened any time by clicking on <strong>Home</strong> icon at the top of each panel.
    Setup current home directory by clicking on <strong>'Set current path as Home'</strong> in context menu.
</div>

<div class="clear">
    <br><br>
    Use <span style="background-color: #008080; padding:0;"> &lt; </span> and <span style="background-color: #008080; padding:0;"> &gt; </span>
    buttons (near current path of each panel) to open current path (selected on active panel) on inactive panel. This option is not available for panel, which opened archive file.
</div>

<div>
    <div class="floatLeftDiv">
        <img src="full_path.png" alt="Panels"/>
    </div>
    <div class="floatText">
        Long click on full path label (on the top of each panel) will open popup window with all sub-folders of current path. It may be used for quick navigation (by clicking on certain directory in path).
    </div>
</div>

<div class="clear">
    <br><br>
    <a href="far_help/help">Home</a>
</div>
